candidates.body:
Because why not.

**Warning**
This will break if you use old Python code as library or module, I'm not planning to publish this crates to `crates.io` but you can use direct github to use each crates which contains the implementation of each sources.

Rust crates will start to use `0.2.0` version and up

**TODOs**:
- [x] Implement macros/helper (`tosho_macros`)
- [x] KC KM (`tosho_kmkc`)
	- [x] Models/DTOs
    	- [x] Account/users
    	- [x] Enums
    	- [x] Titles
    	- [x] Episodes
    	- [x] Others
	- [x] Imaging
    	- [ ] Optimize image size?
	- [x] Errors
	- [x] Constants
	- [x] Config
	- [x] Client
    	- [x] Hashing function
    	- [x] Mobile route (no different to web actually)
    	- [x] Web route
    	- [x] Login by username/password?
- [x] SQ MU! (`tosho_musq`)
    - [x] Proto
    	- [x] Account/user
    	- [x] Chapter
    	- [x] Manga
    	- [x] Enums
    	- [x] Point related
    - [x] Helper
    - [x] Constants
    - [x] Config (almost none actually, will be moved to CLI)
- [x] CLI (`tosho`)

Chores:
- [x] Github CI for linting and tests.
	- [ ] Implement coverage?
- [x] Implement GitHub CI for auto building and releases system ~~(after everything has been merged, put it in separate PR)~~
- [x] Create another branch to host legacy Python code
	- [x] Delete Python code from this branch
	
Closes: #8
